        "finger": "The finger awareness practice was again the most tangible tool. When I noticed the index finger relaxing, it was a direct indicator that my attention had migrated away from the *meaning* of the chant and onto the *task* of counting. The act of straightening the finger was a very small, physical intervention. It wasn't a deep shift in awareness, but it functioned as a precise, immediate tether. It reminded me that the point of contact\u2014the physical reality of the finger\u2014was present, pulling the scattered awareness back toward the immediate sensory input. It was a minor course correction, a small, manageable point of contact amid the auditory flow.",
